			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">BNROM, GNROM, and ANROM are all well-known discrete logic mappers that support banking $E000-$FFFF (albeit at the same time as the rest of $8000-$FFFF).<br /><br />The 74'161 used by these discrete logic mappers is <em>most likely</em> to power up with all 0s, but the value is unchanged on reset. A debugging emulator should probably randomize the bank on powerup. An emulator trying to not tickle any bugs should probably cold boot into bank 0.<br /><br />For mappers that support banking the upper 8KiB of CPU address space but are not based on the 74'161 (e.g. MMC1, MMC5, m97, 137, 138, 139, 141, 246) the behavior differs.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

