						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Power isn't disconnected from anywhere during a reset, so memory isn't affected and the currently swapped-in bank stays there. I</div><br />This is false. Discrete logic mappers use R+C+Diode circuit on M2 line to detect reset, so  memory got unchanged but chips that are sensible on reset and holds bank data are reset thus currently swapped bank might get changed.</div>

